<taxonomicName id="A6D04D30FFCE7866FE46FAB5FCF2FAFB" authority="Bigot, 1889" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1889" box="[407,866,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Rhinophoridae" genus="Tromodesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis">
<emphasis id="53A4EAA1FFCE7866FE46FAB5FD43FAFB" box="[407,723,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Tromodesia haemorrhoidalis</emphasis>
Bigot, 1889
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="A6D04D30FFCE7866FC41FAB5FBECFAFB" authorityName="de Santis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[912,1148,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Ophirodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrifrons">
<emphasis id="53A4EAA1FFCE7866FC41FAB5FBECFAFB" box="[912,1148,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Ophirodexia atrifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from NHM-UK in good condition, but lower part of head partly covered by mould (
<figureCitation id="F9EB2A36FFCE7866FF79FA4FFE92FA3D" box="[168,258,1445,1470]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[160,225,1675,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1153,696,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-154@3.[162,1154,696,1643]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Tromodesia haemorrhoidalis Bigot, 1889 (= Ophirodexia atrifrons Wiedemann, 1830) holotype ♂. (a) Dorsal habitus. (b) Head, frontal view. (c) Lateral habitus. (d) Labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5469904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5469904/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(b)), front legs missing, one mid leg missing and tarsus missing, one hind leg missing and tibia and tarsus missing, left wing damaged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="616F36B3FFCE7866FF71F9F6FC9FF943" blockId="5.[160,1155,1564,1728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis id="53A4EAA1FFCE7866FF71F9F6FF4FF9B5" bold="true" box="[160,223,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Note.</emphasis>
The synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="A6D04D30FFCE7866FE6CF9F7FD66F9B5" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1889" box="[445,758,1565,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Rhinophoridae" genus="Tromodesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis">
<emphasis id="53A4EAA1FFCE7866FE6CF9F7FD66F9B5" box="[445,758,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Tromodesia haemorrhoidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="A6D04D30FFCE7866FCEBF9F7FC74F9B5" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[826,996,1565,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrifrons">
<emphasis id="53A4EAA1FFCE7866FCEBF9F7FC74F9B5" box="[826,996,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Musca atrifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="05414B42FFCE7866FEDEF9D5FDECF9DB" author="Brauer F &amp; Bergenstamm JE" box="[271,636,1599,1624]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="152" refId="ref4656" refString="Brauer F, Bergenstamm JE. 1893. Die Zweiflugler des Kaiserlichen Museums zu Wien. VI. Vorarbeiten zu einer Monographie der Muscaria schizometopa (exclusive Anthomyidae). Pars III. F. Wien: Tempsky; p. 152." type="book chapter" year="1893">Brauer and Bergenstamm (1893)</bibRefCitation>
, and was later confirmed by Townsend (1939) and 
<bibRefCitation id="05414B42FFCE7866FF01F988FE04F9F8" author="Guimaraes JH" box="[208,404,1634,1659]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="333" refId="ref4852" refString="Guimaraes JH. 1971. Family Tachinidae (Larvaevoridae). A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas South of the United States. Vol. 104. Sao Paulo: Departamento de Zoologia, Secretaria da Agricultura, Sao Paulo; p. 333." type="book chapter" year="1971">Guimarães (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. After consulting the redescription of the 
<typeStatus id="BE6B8811FFCE7866FCB0F988FC55F9F8" box="[865,965,1634,1659]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="A6D04D30FFCE7866FC36F988FBF2F9F8" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[999,1122,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrifrons">
<emphasis id="53A4EAA1FFCE7866FC36F988FBF2F9F8" box="[999,1122,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">M. atrifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Aldrich (1929) and comparing it with the 
<typeStatus id="BE6B8811FFCE7866FDB6F96FFD5BF91D" box="[615,715,1669,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="A6D04D30FFCE7866FD3CF96FFC26F91D" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1889" box="[749,950,1669,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Rhinophoridae" genus="Tromodesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis">
<emphasis id="53A4EAA1FFCE7866FD3CF96FFC26F91D" box="[749,950,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">T. haemorrhoidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is clear that this synonymy is correct and it is therefore followed herein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="29CA6538FFCD7865FF71FF64FE18FEB0" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="616F36B3FFCD7865FF71FF64FE18FEB0" blockId="6.[160,1156,142,307]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="53A4EAA1FFCD7865FF71FF64FE8AFF2B" bold="true" box="[160,282,142,168]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head with pedicel entirely brownish black (
<figureCitation id="F9EB2A36FFCD7865FCCBFF65FCE4FF2B" box="[794,884,143,168]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[160,225,1675,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1153,696,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-154@3.[162,1154,696,1643]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Tromodesia haemorrhoidalis Bigot, 1889 (= Ophirodexia atrifrons Wiedemann, 1830) holotype ♂. (a) Dorsal habitus. (b) Head, frontal view. (c) Lateral habitus. (d) Labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5469904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5469904/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(b)); fronto-orbital plate with very small setulae along its extension; parafacial silvery to slightly golden pruinosity; syntergite 1 + 2 to tergite 4 brownish black, without median brown longitudinal vitta; silver pruinosity covering almost all tergites (
<figureCitation id="F9EB2A36FFCD7865FD6CFF1DFC89FE93" box="[701,793,247,272]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[160,225,1675,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1153,696,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-154@3.[162,1154,696,1643]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Tromodesia haemorrhoidalis Bigot, 1889 (= Ophirodexia atrifrons Wiedemann, 1830) holotype ♂. (a) Dorsal habitus. (b) Head, frontal view. (c) Lateral habitus. (d) Labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5469904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5469904/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(a,c)); tergite 5 reddish brown apically (
<figureCitation id="F9EB2A36FFCD7865FED2FEF0FECBFEB0" box="[259,347,282,307]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[160,225,1675,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1153,696,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-154@3.[162,1154,696,1643]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Tromodesia haemorrhoidalis Bigot, 1889 (= Ophirodexia atrifrons Wiedemann, 1830) holotype ♂. (a) Dorsal habitus. (b) Head, frontal view. (c) Lateral habitus. (d) Labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5469904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5469904/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(c)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
